        "content": [
          "WEAK ENDINGS (after der/die/das):",
          "",
          "         Masc    Fem     Neut    Plural",
          "NOM:     -e      -e      -e      -en",
          "ACC:     -en     -e      -e      -en",
          "DAT:     -en     -en     -en     -en",
          "GEN:     -en     -en     -en     -en",
          "",
          "NOMINATIVE EXAMPLE:",
          "der elegante Mann",
          "die elegante Frau",
          "das elegante Kleid",
          "die eleganten Leute",
          "",
          "'WEAK' ENDINGS EXPLAINED:",
          "Why 'weak'? The article already",
          "expresses gender and case. The",
          "adjective just tags along."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion siebenundzwanzig"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "MIXED ENDINGS (after ein/eine/kein/mein):",
          "",
          "         Masc    Fem     Neut    Plural",
          "NOM:     -er     -e      -es     -en",
          "ACC:     -en     -e      -es     -en",
          "DAT:     -en     -en     -en     -en",
          "GEN:     -en     -en     -en     -en",
          "",
          "NOMINATIVE:",
          "ein eleganter Mann",
          "eine elegante Frau",
          "ein elegantes Kleid",
          "keine eleganten Leute",
          "",
          "ACCUSATIVE:",
          "Ich sehe einen eleganten Mann.",
          "Ich sehe eine elegante Frau.",
          "Ich sehe ein elegantes Kleid.",
          "Ich sehe keine eleganten Leute.",
          "",
          "Masculine NOM: -er, Neuter NOM/ACC: -es",
          "Masculine ACC: -en (the -en shows it's accusative)"
